Good to know: The children prop is an implicit slot that does not need to be mapped to a folder. This means app/page.js is
equivalent to app/@children/page.js. Unmatched Routes
By default, the content rendered within a slot will match the current URL. In the case of an unmatched slot, the content that Next.js renders differs based on the routing technique and folder structure. default.jsdefault.js
You can define a default.js file to render as a fallback when Next.js cannot recover a slots active state based on the current URL. Consider the following folder structure. The @team slot has a settings directory, but @analytics does not.","textTemplate":"","metadataSeparator":"
