Since v10.2.1 Next.js supports incremental type checking when enabled in your tsconfig.json, this can help speed up type
checking in larger applications. Ignoring TypeScript Errors
Next.js fails your production build (next build) when TypeScript errors are present in your project. If youd like Next.js to dangerously produce production code even when your application has errors, you can disable the built-in type
checking step. If disabled, be sure you are running type checks as part of your build or deploy process, otherwise this can be very dangerous. Open next.config.js and enable the ignoreBuildErrors option in the typescript config:
