The pages directory uses getServerSideProps and getStaticProps to fetch data for pages. Inside the app directory, these previous
data fetching functions are replaced with a simpler API built on top of fetch() and async React Server Components. app/page.tsx (tsx)export default async function Page() {
  // This request should be cached until manually invalidated. // Similar to `getStaticProps`. // `force-cache` is the default and can be omitted. const staticData = await fetch(`https://...`, { cache: 'force-cache' })
