Responsive image with fillfill
If you dont know the aspect ratio, you will need to set the fill prop and set position: relative on the parent. Optionally, you can
set object-fit style depending on the desired stretch vs crop behavior:
app/page.js (jsx)import Image from 'next/image'
export default function Page({ photoUrl }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ position: 'relative', width: '500px', height: '300px' }}>
      <Image
        src={photoUrl}
        alt="Picture of the author"
        sizes="500px"
        fill
        style={{
          objectFit: 'contain',
        }}
      />
    </div>
  )
}
