Description: Fetch dynamic data on the server for your React component with getInitialProps. Good to know: getInitialProps is a legacy API. We recommend using getStaticProps or getServerSideProps instead. getInitialProps is an async function that can be added to the default exported React component for the page. It will run on both
the server-side and again on the client-side during page transitions. The result of the function will be forwarded to the React
component as props. pages/index.tsx (tsx)import { NextPageContext } from 'next'
