swcPlugins accepts an array of tuples for configuring plugins. A tuple for the plugin contains the path to the plugin and an object for
plugin configuration. The path to the plugin can be an npm module package name or an absolute path to the .wasm binary itself. Unsupported Features
When your application has a .babelrc file, Next.js will automatically fall back to using Babel for transforming individual files. This
ensures backwards compatibility with existing applications that leverage custom Babel plugins. If youre using a custom Babel setup, please share your configuration. Were working to port as many commonly used Babel
transformations as possible, as well as supporting plugins in the future. Version History
